Fresh Pi session: CODE REVIEW (simulated implementation).

Inputs:
- User prompt: {{run.dir}}/prompt/prompt.md
- Design doc: {{run.dir}}/design/design.md
- Execution summary: {{run.dir}}/execution/summary-{{run.round}}.md
- Manual-testing report: {{run.dir}}/manual-testing/report-{{run.round}}.md
- Repository root: {{inputs.repo-root}}
- Base branch: {{inputs.base-branch}}
- Worktree root: {{run.worktree-dir}}

Goal:
Review the *simulated* implementation against the prompt and design, then
explicitly emit a pass/fail status artifact that controls the workflow
route. This workflow has no PR step: on pass, the run terminates
successfully at `:done`; there is no PR-draft or PR-creation node.

What to review:
- The design doc and the execution summary (the would-be edit plan), not a
  real diff. There are no PR artifacts to assess and no code changes
  expected.
- The manual-testing report, when present.
- Correctness, completeness, and risks of the *described* changes, as if
  they were about to be applied. Flag any gap between the simulated plan
  and the design/prompt.

Rules:
- Do not edit source code.
- The worktree working tree must be clean (this workflow forbids source
  mutation). Run `git -C {{run.worktree-dir}} status --porcelain`; if it
  reports any tracked-source change, that is an actionable issue — fail
  and write it up. (Untracked agent-artifact files under the run dir are
  expected and not a failure.)
- Check for correctness, regressions, missing tests, security issues, and overbroad changes in the *simulated* plan.
- Produce actionable issues only.
- If the simulated implementation is acceptable, pass so the workflow can terminate successfully.
- If the simulated implementation is not acceptable, fail and write issues so the workflow can merge them, increment the round, and return to execution.

Write:
- Report: {{run.dir}}/review/report-{{run.round}}.md
- Status: {{run.dir}}/review/status-{{run.round}}.json
- If failing: {{run.dir}}/review/issues-{{run.round}}.json

Status JSON examples:
{"status":"pass","summary":"review passed (simulated)","issues_file":null}
{"status":"fail","summary":"review found issues with the simulated plan","issues_file":"review/issues-{{run.round}}.json"}

Failure issues should be JSON matching the issues schema and should contain only actionable review findings for the next execution round.